    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>School or style associated with a group of artists surrounding Utagawa Toyoharu, including Hiroshige. The Utagawa School was influential and was the most popular print house in 19th century Japan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
